===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|i}} – hill. Earlier form closer to {{zh-l|*丠}}, as in {{och-l|虛}}. Compare {{zh-l|*山}}.

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-ref|Wang (1982)}} relates this word to {{zh-l|墟}} "ruin-mound". {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} considers two homophones [[丘]], "hill, mound" & [[丘]] "village, district" to be the same word as settlements were often built on elevated grounds (for a parallel see {{zh-l|京}}). 

From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*r/g-wa||village}}; within Sinitic, {{och-l|丘}} is cognate with {{och-l|里}} "village" & {{och-l|街}} "road crossing, street"; outsides Sinitic, cognate with {{cog|lus|khua||village}}, {{cog|cnh|khûa||village, cosmos}}, {{cog|my|ရွာ||village}} (STEDT).

